title: UMD Volleyball Slide to No. 8 in AVCA Poll
text:
UMD Volleyball Slide to No. 8 in AVCA Poll 
By Zach Schneider UMD Volleyball Slide to No. 8 in AVCA Poll October 19, 2015 Updated Oct 19, 2015 at 3:10 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- The University of Minnesota Duluth (UMD) volleyball team dropped three spots to No. 8 in this week's American Volleyball Coaches' Association (AVCA) Division II poll, which was released on Monday afternoon. 
The Bulldogs still received a single first-place vote in the poll, but the drop comes after UMD was swept by Wayne State on its home floor as part of a (1-1) weekend. 
Click here to subscribe to our daily newsletter. 
For full results of this week's AVCA II poll, click here. 
UMD has three road matches scheduled for this week, including a rematch with No. 4 Concordia-St. Paul on Oct. 23.
